Electronics (3 docs)
| Document | Key Design Decisions |
|---|---|
| Sony Headphones | Nested specifications.microphone, variants[] array with per-colour stock, ratings.breakdown object |
| Samsung TV | Nested dimensions_cm + weight_kg objects, hdr_support[] array, installation sub-object |
| Apple MacBook Air | Nested processor + display objects, emi_options[] array with month/rate details, ports[] array |
Clothing (3 docs)
| Document | Key Design Decisions |
|---|---|
| Men's Shirt | variants[] with per-colour sizes[] arrays each holding chest measurement + stock |
| Women's Kurta | set_includes[], dual fabric fields (kurta vs dupatta), per-variant bust/waist measurements |
| Running Shoes | Both UK and EU sizing inside each sizes[] entry, activity[] array, biomechanical drop_mm field |
Groceries (3 docs)
| Document | Key Design Decisions |
|---|---|
| Tata Tea | nutritional_info_per_100g, certifications[], shelf_life with opened/unopened distinction |
| Amul Milk | subscription_options[] array with frequency + discount, refrigerated shelf life tracking |
| Fortune Oil | Full fat breakdown in nutrition (saturated/poly/mono/trans), suitable_for[] array, fortified_with[] |
The document model deliberately avoids the joins that would be required in a relational schema — all attributes relevant to a product live in one document, which is the core strength of MongoDB for product catalogues.
